<section class="mx-auto max-w-[1240px] px-6 pb-10 pt-16 sm:px-10 sm:pt-24">
  <p class="mb-5 font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-flame">
    The 100-mile info project · Western States 100 · June 27, 2026
  </p>
  <h1 class="mb-5 max-w-3xl text-balance text-4xl font-black uppercase leading-[0.95] tracking-tight sm:text-6xl">
    One place for everything Western States.
  </h1>
  <p class="max-w-2xl text-lg font-medium leading-relaxed text-stone">
    The schedule, the course map, aid stations, crew access, and where to follow along —
    pulled out of a dozen old race-site links and laid out plainly. Free and open source.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="mx-auto max-w-[1240px] px-6 pb-20 sm:px-10">
  <h2 class="mb-6 font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-stone">I'm here to…</h2>
  <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-3">
    <%= render "home/role_card", href: runner_path, label: "Run it",
          blurb: "Schedule, cutoffs, the lottery & registration link, the GPX course, and what to expect out there." %>
    <%= render "home/role_card", href: crew_path, label: "Crew or pace",
          blurb: "Which aid stations allow crew, the crew-access map, parking & shuttles, drop bags, and ETA splits." %>
    <%= render "home/role_card", href: follow_path, label: "Follow along",
          blurb: "Live tracking, the best spots to watch from, and the full schedule for race day." %>
  </div>

  <p class="mt-10 text-sm text-stone">
    Built by one runner. No ads, no accounts, no upsell — just the info.
    <a href="#about" class="font-semibold text-ink underline-offset-2 hover:text-flame">Why this exists →</a>
  </p>
</section>
